39#ifndef CHANNEL_H
40#define CHANNEL_H
41
42/* Definitions for channel types. */
43#define SSH_CHANNEL_X11_LISTENER 1 /* Listening for inet X11 conn. */
44#define SSH_CHANNEL_PORT_LISTENER 2 /* Listening on a port. */
45#define SSH_CHANNEL_OPENING 3 /* waiting for confirmation */
46#define SSH_CHANNEL_OPEN 4 /* normal open two-way channel */
47#define SSH_CHANNEL_CLOSED 5 /* waiting for close confirmation */
48#define SSH_CHANNEL_AUTH_SOCKET 6 /* authentication socket */
49#define SSH_CHANNEL_X11_OPEN 7 /* reading first X11 packet */
50#define SSH_CHANNEL_LARVAL 10 /* larval session */
51#define SSH_CHANNEL_RPORT_LISTENER 11 /* Listening to a R-style port */
52#define SSH_CHANNEL_CONNECTING 12
53#define SSH_CHANNEL_DYNAMIC 13
54#define SSH_CHANNEL_ZOMBIE 14 /* Almost dead. */
55#define SSH_CHANNEL_MUX_LISTENER 15 /* Listener for mux conn. */
56#define SSH_CHANNEL_MUX_CLIENT 16 /* Conn. to mux slave */
57#define SSH_CHANNEL_ABANDONED 17 /* Abandoned session, eg mux */
58#define SSH_CHANNEL_UNIX_LISTENER 18 /* Listening on a domain socket. */
59#define SSH_CHANNEL_RUNIX_LISTENER 19 /* Listening to a R-style domain socket. */
60#define SSH_CHANNEL_MUX_PROXY 20 /* proxy channel for mux-slave */
61#define SSH_CHANNEL_RDYNAMIC_OPEN 21 /* reverse SOCKS, parsing request */
62#define SSH_CHANNEL_RDYNAMIC_FINISH 22 /* reverse SOCKS, finishing connect */
63#define SSH_CHANNEL_MAX_TYPE 23
64
65#define CHANNEL_CANCEL_PORT_STATIC -1
66
67/* TCP forwarding */
68#define FORWARD_DENY 0
69#define FORWARD_REMOTE (1)
70#define FORWARD_LOCAL (1<<1)
71#define FORWARD_ALLOW (FORWARD_REMOTE|FORWARD_LOCAL)
72
73#define FORWARD_ADM 0x100
74#define FORWARD_USER 0x101

76struct ssh;
77struct Channel;
78typedef struct Channel Channel;
79struct fwd_perm_list;

81typedef void channel_open_fn(struct ssh *, int, int, void *);
82typedef void channel_callback_fn(struct ssh *, int, void *);
83typedef int channel_infilter_fn(struct ssh *, struct Channel *, const char *,
84 int);
85typedef void channel_filter_cleanup_fn(struct ssh *, int, void *);
86typedef u_char *channel_outfilter_fn(struct ssh *, struct Channel *,
87 u_char **, size_t *);
88
89/* Channel success/failure callbacks */
90typedef void channel_confirm_cb(struct ssh *, int, struct Channel *, void *);
91typedef void channel_confirm_abandon_cb(struct ssh *, struct Channel *, void *);
92struct channel_confirm {
93 TAILQ_ENTRY(channel_confirm) entry;
94 channel_confirm_cb *cb;
95 channel_confirm_abandon_cb *abandon_cb;
96 void *ctx;
97};
98TAILQ_HEAD(channel_confirms, channel_confirm);
99
100/* Context for non-blocking connects */
101struct channel_connect {
102 char *host;
103 int port;
104 struct addrinfo *ai, *aitop;
105};
106
107/* Callbacks for mux channels back into client-specific code */
108typedef int mux_callback_fn(struct ssh *, struct Channel *);
109
110struct Channel {
111 int type; /* channel type/state */
112 int self; /* my own channel identifier */
113 uint32_t remote_id; /* channel identifier for remote peer */
114 int have_remote_id; /* non-zero if remote_id is valid */
115
116 u_int istate; /* input from channel (state of receive half) */
117 u_int ostate; /* output to channel (state of transmit half) */
118 int flags; /* close sent/rcvd */
119 int rfd; /* read fd */
120 int wfd; /* write fd */
121 int efd; /* extended fd */
122 int sock; /* sock fd */
123 int ctl_chan; /* control channel (multiplexed connections) */
124 int isatty; /* rfd is a tty */
125 int client_tty; /* (client) TTY has been requested */
126 int force_drain; /* force close on iEOF */
127 time_t notbefore; /* Pause IO until deadline (time_t) */
128 int delayed; /* post-select handlers for newly created
129 * channels are delayed until the first call
130 * to a matching pre-select handler.
131 * this way post-select handlers are not
132 * accidentally called if a FD gets reused */
133 struct sshbuf *input; /* data read from socket, to be sent over
134 * encrypted connection */
135 struct sshbuf *output; /* data received over encrypted connection for
136 * send on socket */
137 struct sshbuf *extended;
138
139 char *path;
140 /* path for unix domain sockets, or host name for forwards */
141 int listening_port; /* port being listened for forwards */
142 char *listening_addr; /* addr being listened for forwards */
143 int host_port; /* remote port to connect for forwards */
144 char *remote_name; /* remote hostname */
145
146 u_int remote_window;
147 u_int remote_maxpacket;
148 u_int local_window;
149 u_int local_window_max;
150 u_int local_consumed;
151 u_int local_maxpacket;
152 int dynamic_window;
153 int extended_usage;
154 int single_connection;
155 u_int tcpwinsz;
156
157 char *ctype; /* type */
158
159 /* callback */
160 channel_open_fn *open_confirm;
161 void *open_confirm_ctx;
162 channel_callback_fn *detach_user;
163 int detach_close;
164 struct channel_confirms status_confirms;
165
166 /* filter */
167 channel_infilter_fn *input_filter;
168 channel_outfilter_fn *output_filter;
169 void *filter_ctx;
170 channel_filter_cleanup_fn *filter_cleanup;
171
172 /* keep boundaries */
173 int datagram;
174
175 /* non-blocking connect */
176 /* XXX make this a pointer so the structure can be opaque */
177 struct channel_connect connect_ctx;
178
179 /* multiplexing protocol hook, called for each packet received */
180 mux_callback_fn *mux_rcb;
181 void *mux_ctx;
182 int mux_pause;
183 int mux_downstream_id;
184};
185
186#define CHAN_EXTENDED_IGNORE 0
187#define CHAN_EXTENDED_READ 1
188#define CHAN_EXTENDED_WRITE 2
189
190/* default window/packet sizes for tcp/x11-fwd-channel */
191#define CHAN_SES_PACKET_DEFAULT (32*1024)
192#define CHAN_SES_WINDOW_DEFAULT (4*CHAN_SES_PACKET_DEFAULT)
193
194#define CHAN_TCP_PACKET_DEFAULT (32*1024)
195#define CHAN_TCP_WINDOW_DEFAULT (4*CHAN_TCP_PACKET_DEFAULT)
196
197#define CHAN_X11_PACKET_DEFAULT (16*1024)
198#define CHAN_X11_WINDOW_DEFAULT (4*CHAN_X11_PACKET_DEFAULT)
199
200/* possible input states */
201#define CHAN_INPUT_OPEN 0
202#define CHAN_INPUT_WAIT_DRAIN 1
203#define CHAN_INPUT_WAIT_OCLOSE 2
204#define CHAN_INPUT_CLOSED 3
205
206/* possible output states */
207#define CHAN_OUTPUT_OPEN 0
208#define CHAN_OUTPUT_WAIT_DRAIN 1
209#define CHAN_OUTPUT_WAIT_IEOF 2
210#define CHAN_OUTPUT_CLOSED 3
211
212#define CHAN_CLOSE_SENT 0x01
213#define CHAN_CLOSE_RCVD 0x02
214#define CHAN_EOF_SENT 0x04
215#define CHAN_EOF_RCVD 0x08
216#define CHAN_LOCAL 0x10
217
218/* Read buffer size */
219#define CHAN_RBUF (16*1024)
220
221/* Hard limit on number of channels */
222#define CHANNELS_MAX_CHANNELS (16*1024)
223
224/* check whether 'efd' is still in use */
225#define CHANNEL_EFD_INPUT_ACTIVE(c) \
226 (c->extended_usage == CHAN_EXTENDED_READ && \
227 (c->efd != -1 || \
228 sshbuf_len(c->extended) > 0))
229#define CHANNEL_EFD_OUTPUT_ACTIVE(c) \
230 (c->extended_usage == CHAN_EXTENDED_WRITE && \
231 c->efd != -1 && (!(c->flags & (CHAN_EOF_RCVD|CHAN_CLOSE_RCVD)) || \
232 sshbuf_len(c->extended) > 0))
